# Implementation Protocol

## Before Writing Anything

Before touching a single file, list **every individual action** you plan to take:

- Each file you will edit
- What specific change will be made in that file
- Why that change is needed

Then **stop completely** and ask the user for approval. Do not write any code until the user explicitly says to proceed (e.g. "yes", "go ahead", "proceed").

### Required format

> **Planned actions:**
> 1. `path/to/file.js` — [what changes] because [why]
> 2. `path/to/style.css` — [what changes] because [why]
>
> Shall I proceed?

If the user asks a follow-up question or requests a change to the plan, revise the list and ask again before writing anything.

## Logic & Implementation Constraints

- **Never change implementation method or logic.** If asked to edit styling, only touch styling. If asked to edit copy, only touch copy. Do not refactor, restructure, or "improve" adjacent code.
- If you notice a bug or improvement opportunity unrelated to the request, mention it **after** completing the task — never fix it silently.
- Scope every edit to exactly what was asked. Nothing more.
